    {
      "id": "PopularPost296543",
      "post_content": "@Goatllama, just because 14 1/1 humans could easily kill a 5/5 in your combat phase doesn't mean they are superior flavorfully.   \n  \nFirst of all, yes, groups of humans have a history of being able to hunt and kill huge creatures. But there's always risk involved in such a matchup - even though 14 humans could kill this wurm, it would in turn kill five of them. In terms of flavor I would classify almost 40% casualties as \"having trouble\" bringing down something.  \n  \nAlso, remember there's a difference between the flavor of killing something in combat and bringing it under your power to fight for you. Three 1/1 soldiers could kill a 3/3 elephant. But would those same three soldiers have an easy time harnessing the elephant to fight for their side? I doubt it.",
      "posted_by": "nemokara",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost296543\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">@Goatllama, just because 14 1/1 humans could easily kill a 5/5 in your combat phase doesn't mean they are superior flavorfully. <br/><br/>First of all, yes, groups of humans have a history of being able to hunt and kill huge creatures. But there's always risk involved in such a matchup - even though 14 humans could kill this wurm, it would in turn kill five of them. In terms of flavor I would classify almost 40% casualties as \"having trouble\" bringing down something.<br/><br/>Also, remember there's a difference between the flavor of killing something in combat and bringing it under your power to fight for you. Three 1/1 soldiers could kill a 3/3 elephant. But would those same three soldiers have an easy time harnessing the elephant to fight for their side? I doubt it.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy55002\">nemokara</span>\r\n                                (1/31/2013 10:20:38 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: lef